<title>USA: Watson Pharmaceutical buys Dilacor rights.</title>
<headline>Watson Pharmaceutical buys Dilacor rights.</headline>
<dateline>CORONA, Calif. 1997-06-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Watson Pharmaceuticals Inc said Monday it acquired exclusive worldwide rights to Rhone-Poulenc Rorer Inc's Dilacor treatment for hypertension and unstable angina, for a total consideration of about $190 million.</p>
<p>It said the price reflects an annual licensing fee and a royalty on sales over the 4-1/2 year licensing period. The agreement excludes certain markets in the U.S., where Rhone-Poulenc will continue to market the treatment.</p>
